PART II: THE 4-POINT EIGENVALUE CORRELATOR
========================================================================

The 4-point correlator:
  Cв‚„(i,j,k,l) = ОЈ_t sin(2ПЂit/p) sin(2ПЂjt/p) sin(2ПЂkt/p) sin(2ПЂlt/p)

This is the "spectral 4-point function" вЂ” it measures how much
the 4 sine waves (corresponding to chords i,j,k,l) overlap in
the eigenvalue spectrum.

Using product-to-sum formulas:
  4 sin A sin B sin C sin D =
  cos(A-B-C+D) + cos(A-B+C-D) + cos(A+B-C-D)
  - cos(A+B+C+D) - cos(A-B-C-D) - cos(A+B-C+D) - cos(A-B+C+D)
  + cos(A+B+C-D)

Actually, let's just use:
  sin a В· sin b = [cos(a-b) - cos(a+b)]/2

Applied twice:
  sin a sin b sin c sin d = (1/4)[cos(a-b) - cos(a+b)][cos(c-d) - cos(c+d)]

So Cв‚„ involves sums of cos(2ПЂ(В±iВ±jВ±kВ±l)t/p).

By orthogonality: ОЈ_t cos(2ПЂnt/p) = p if nв‰Ў0 mod p, else 0.

So Cв‚„ = (p/4) В· #{В±iВ±jВ±kВ±l в‰Ў 0 mod p} / 4.

